{"image_id": "SYK_2006_page_59", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "57", "bbox": [1158.8, 1573.9, 1175.0, 1588.5]}, {"text": "NOTE 9", "bbox": [150.0, 248.8, 217.4, 265.5]}, {"text": "RETIREMENT PLANS", "bbox": [150.0, 278.0, 339.3, 294.7]}, {"text": "Certain of the Company’s subsidiaries have both funded and unfunded deﬁned beneﬁt pension plans covering some or all of their", "bbox": [150.0, 334.6, 1175.2, 354.4]}, {"text": "employees. All of the deﬁned beneﬁt pension plans have projected beneﬁt obligations in excess of plan assets. As discussed in Note 1,", "bbox": [150.0, 363.8, 1175.0, 383.5]}, {"text": "the Company adopted the provisions of FASB Statement No. 158 as of December 31, 2006. The adoption of the Statement did not", "bbox": [150.0, 392.9, 1175.0, 412.7]}, {"text": "require a restatement of prior periods. Substantially all of the deﬁned beneﬁt pension plans use a December 31 measurement date", "bbox": [150.0, 422.1, 1175.0, 441.9]}, {"text": "for the determination of plan obligations and funded status of the plans.A summary of the Company’s deﬁned beneﬁt pension plans", "bbox": [150.0, 451.3, 1175.0, 471.0]}, {"text": "is as follows (in millions):", "bbox": [150.0, 480.4, 352.0, 500.2]}, {"text": "December 31", "bbox": [1062.2, 530.9, 1133.7, 544.5]}, {"text": "2006", "bbox": [1033.6, 555.4, 1075.4, 575.2]}, {"text": "2005", "bbox": [1137.8, 555.4, 1179.6, 575.2]}, {"text": "Change in projected beneﬁt obligations:", "bbox": [150.0, 584.6, 464.8, 604.4]}, {"text": "Projected beneﬁt obligations at beginning of year", "bbox": [175.0, 613.8, 561.6, 633.5]}, {"text": "$156.8", "bbox": [1016.6, 613.8, 1068.8, 633.5]}, {"text": "$145.3", "bbox": [1119.7, 613.8, 1177.4, 633.5]}, {"text": "Service cost", "bbox": [175.0, 642.9, 267.0, 662.7]}, {"text": "10.7", "bbox": [1035.5, 642.9, 1068.8, 662.7]}, {"text": "8.6", "bbox": [1149.2, 642.9, 1177.5, 662.7]}, {"text": "Interest cost", "bbox": [175.0, 672.1, 270.6, 691.9]}, {"text": "6.9", "bbox": [1045.